early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud de Ramsbury married Roger Peyvre before 1204, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–1205":"–1205","1204–Male":"1204–Surnud","1205–1251":"1205–1251","–Female":"Surnud","before 1204":"enne 1204","1205":"1205","1204":"1204","about 1204":"umbes 1204","1251":"1251","Chalton, Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalton, Bedfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–1205":"–1205","1204–Male":"1204–Kuollut","1205–1251":"1205–1251","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1204":"ennen vuotta 1204","1205":"1205","1204":"1204","about 1204":"noin 1204","1251":"1251","Chalton, Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalton, Bedfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–1205":"–1205","1204–Male":"1204–Décédé","1205–1251":"1205–1251","–Female":"Décédée","before 1204":"avant 1204","1205":"1205","1204":"1204","about 1204":"environ 1204","1251":"1251","Chalton, Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalton, Bedfordshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Maud de Ramsbury a épousé Roger Peyvre avant 1204, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–1205":"–1205","1204–Male":"1204–Verstorben","1205–1251":"1205–1251","–Female":"Verstorben","before 1204":"vor 1204","1205":"1205","1204":"1204","about 1204":"um 1204","1251":"1251","Chalton, Toddington, Bedfordshire, England":"Chalton, Bedfordshire, England","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Maud de Ramsbury hat vo